StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(scan.nextLine());
String command = st.nextToken();
int hour = Integer.parseInt(st.nextToken());
int minute = Integer.parseInt(st.nextToken());

Explanation:
The StringTokenizer class is used to break a string into tokens. In this case, the string is the line read from the file. The tokens are separated by spaces. The first token is the command, which is stored in the command variable. The next two tokens are the hour and minute, which are stored in the hour and minute variables. The Integer.parseInt() method is used to convert the tokens to integers.

